[EXAMPLES]
.TP
Scan a directory for duplicate videos:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-v
.EE
.TP
Scan for duplicate images:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/photos \-\-mode image \-v
.EE
.TP
Scan for duplicate audio files:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/music \-\-mode audio \-v
.EE
.TP
Enable perceptual content hashing for higher accuracy:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-\-content \-v
.EE
.TP
Interactive review with trash action:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-i \-\-keep newest \-\-action trash
.EE
.TP
Custom scoring weights:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-\-weights "filename=30,duration=40,resolution=20,filesize=10"
.EE

[FILES]
.TP
.I ~/.config/duplicates\-detector/config.toml
Configuration file (TOML format). Use \fB\-\-save\-config\fR to write current settings.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/duplicates\-detector/ignore.json
Persistent false\-positive ignore list. Managed via interactive review (\fBs!\fR command).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/duplicates\-detector/sessions/
Paused scan sessions for \fB\-\-resume\fR.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/duplicates\-detector/
Metadata, content hash, and audio fingerprint caches.

[EXIT STATUS]
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid arguments.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by Ctrl\-C.

